                                    <button class="btn text-decoration-none text-info" type="button">
                                       	What is the difference between 2D and 3D animation?
                                    </button>
                                    <svg class="svg-inline--fa fa-plus fa-w-14 fa-lg ml-auto mr-3 text-white" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" data-prefix="fa" data-icon="plus" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 448 512" data-fa-i2svg=""><path fill="currentColor" d="M416 208H272V64c0-17.67-14.33-32-32-32h-32c-17.67 0-32 14.33-32 32v144H32c-17.67 0-32 14.33-32 32v32c0 17.67 14.33 32 32 32h144v144c0 17.67 14.33 32 32 32h32c17.67 0 32-14.33 32-32V304h144c17.67 0 32-14.33 32-32v-32c0-17.67-14.33-32-32-32z"></path></svg><!-- <i class="fa fa-plus fa-lg ml-auto mr-3 text-white"></i> -->
                                </div> 
                                <div id="job_body_5" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="job_posting_5" data-parent="#accordion5">
                                    <div class="card-body">
                                        <div class="row">
                                            <div class="col-12 text-white">
                                                <p>The primary difference between 2D (two-dimensional) animation and 3D (three-dimensional) animation lies in the way the images are created and presented. 2D animation has Flat Images, Traditional Animation Techniques and Limited Perspective while 3D animation has Three-Dimensional Space, Key-framing and Rigging and Realistic Depth and Perspective.</p>
                                                <div class=" brdr-0 brdr-left-lightblue  fs-14 p-2 h-auto">

                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
