                        </div><!-- #accordion4 -->
                    </div>
                    <!-- Does VFX in demad as per Job opprtunity ?  -->
                     <div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-lg-12">
                        <div class="accordion" id="accordion12">
                            <div class="brdr-none p-2 bxsh-1 brdr-1">
                                <div class="card-header brdr-none p-2 brdr-2 bxsh-1  d-flex align-items-center " id="job_card_12" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#job_body_12" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="job_body_12">
                                    <button class="btn text-decoration-none text-info" type="button">
                                       	What is the average salary of a VFX artist?
                                    </button>
                                     <svg class="svg-inline--fa fa-plus fa-w-14 fa-lg ml-auto mr-3 text-white" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" data-prefix="fa" data-icon="plus" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 448 512" data-fa-i2svg=""><path fill="currentColor" d="M416 208H272V64c0-17.67-14.33-32-32-32h-32c-17.67 0-32 14.33-32 32v144H32c-17.67 0-32 14.33-32 32v32c0 17.67 14.33 32 32 32h144v144c0 17.67 14.33 32 32 32h32c17.67 0 32-14.33 32-32V304h144c17.67 0 32-14.33 32-32v-32c0-17.67-14.33-32-32-32z"></path></svg><!-- <i class="fa fa-plus fa-lg ml-auto mr-3 text-white"></i> -->
                                </div> 
                                <div id="job_body_12" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="job_posting_12" data-parent="#accordion12">
                                    <div class="card-body">
								 	    <div class="row">
                                            <div class="col-12 text-white">
                                                <p>Those with less than three years of experience may earn an average annual salary ranging from INR 2,00,000 to INR 5,00,000.Senior VFX artists with more than five years of experience may earn higher salaries, typically ranging from INR 10,00,000 to INR 20,00,000 or more annually The VFX industry in India has been growing, driven by an increase in film, television, gaming, and advertising projects that require high-quality visual effects. Salaries may also vary based on the city, with metropolitan areas generally offering higher compensation.</p>
                                                <div class="brdr-0 brdr-left-lightblue  fs-14 p-2">

                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div> <!-- #job_type_3 -->
                            </div> <!-- .card -->
                        </div><!-- #accordion3 -->
                    </div><!-- End of Job Column 2 --> 
